  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>UtilityCo considers net benefit (as per the assumptions of the prompt) as a key metric for comparison of the two programs. The cumulative net benefit of the programs are -$30.00 for the Opower Feedback Program and $70.00 for the Refrigerator Feedback Program. The net present value of the net benefits are -$24.17 and $50.38 respectively. Based on Net Benefit alone, UtilityCo would want to choose the Refrigerator Feedback Program.</p>

    <p>However, that decision would need to be based on some big assumptions:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>First, that participation rates amongst the general population are equal between the two programs.</li>
      <li>Secondly, that UtilityCo equally values short and long-term benefits and program goals.</li>
      <li>Third, that there will be no other associated costs with either program.</li>
      <li>Fourth, that all kWh are equally valued by UtilityCo. Even refrigerator savings over the course of a year, for example, might not be as highly valued as HVAC savings during the winter and summer months.</li>
