<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">How would you advocate for the Opower Program?</h3>
  </div>  
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>The Opower Program has many benefits for UtilityCo that the Refrigerator Program lacks.</p>

    <h4>Participation Rates</h4>

    <p>The Opower Program is provided at no additional cost to the end customer, as opposed to the Refrigerator Program, which requires a $450 expenditure (post-rebate) from the end customer. The large upfront cost for the Refrigerator Rebate Program will probably exclude many potential participants. So, while the cumulative savings for any one household are greater through the Refrigerator Rebate Program, it is likely that many more people will participate in the Opower Program, resulting in more kWh savings for UtilityCo. UtilityCo could test this hypothesis and make its decision based on findings, or could turn to data on similar programs provided by Opower or an independent third-party.</p>

    <h4>Customer Satisfaction</h4>

    <p>The Opower Feedback Program has some other benefits. The constant feedback with customers could improve customer satisfaction with UtilityCo and strengthen customer loyalty. Customer loyalty is increasingly important for utilities who are competing with distributed power systems.</p>

    <h4>Timing</h4>

    <p>UtilityCo should also consider that the Opower Feedback Program provides big efficiency improvements in years 1-3, saving 50% more kWh than the Refrigerator Rebate Program during that time. UtilityCo may favor saving in early years over later years for cash flow purposes. Similarly, the timing of the savings may be important to UtilityCo. Savings spread evenly over a year (as with a refrigerator) will not help UtilityCo with demand issues as much as savings during summer and winter months. If the Opower Feedback Program helps UtilityCo with peak demand issues, UtilityCo could favor the Opower Program, despite the lower net benefit.</p>

    <h4>No Additional Costs</h4>

    <p>The refrigerator Rebate Program will likely require UtilityCo to incur expenses in addition to the rebates. Marketing initiatives such as POV displays in appliance stores and mailings to homeowners might be required to generate awareness. Similarly, UtilityCo will need to pay for rebate processing and tracking. Conversely, the Opower Feedback Program requires no additional expenditures on the part of UtilityCo.</p>
