  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>The Refrigerator Rebate Program provides the largest net benefit for UtilityCo., both in terms of monetary return and kWh saved.</p>

    <h4>Financial</h4>

    <p>The Refrigerator Rebate Program is the most attractive from almost any financial perspective. It has a savings-to-investment ratio of 2.4, and a net present value benefit of $50.38 per end customer. From a cash flow perspective, the Refrigerator Rebate Program provides consistent and predictable savings each year. All of the costs are incurred upfront, in the first year.</p>

    <h4>Rebate Costs</h4>

    <p>The Refrigerator Program could be less expensive than planned if homeowners purchase the energy efficient refrigerators and neglect to apply for the rebate. UtilityCo should try to discern how many homeowners might purchase an energy efficient refrigerator without applying for a rebate. That could lower their cost and improve their ROI.</p>

    <h4>kWh Savings</h4>

    <p>The savings add up to greater kWh savings per participating home. Refrigerator Rebate Program homes will save 1,200 kWh over 12 years versus 900 kWh for the Opower Feedback Program.</p>

    <h4>Consistent Returns</h4>

    <p>Lastly, the Refrigerator Rebate Program does not suffer from the same diminishing returns as the Opower Feedback Program. Instead, the Refrigerator Rebate Program provides consistent net benefits to UtilityCo.</p>
